      <h1>How to Calculate Your College GPA: Complete Guide</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">Your grade point average is one of the most important numbers in your academic career. It determines eligibility for scholarships, dean's list honors, graduate school admissions, and even some job opportunities after graduation. Yet many students are unsure exactly how their GPA is calculated, what quality points are, or how individual course grades translate into a cumulative number. This guide walks you through every step of the GPA calculation process on the standard 4.0 scale, explains weighted versus unweighted systems, and shows you how to calculate both semester and cumulative GPA with real examples.</p>
    </header>

